The '''ACM Virtual Reality International Conference''' ('''VRIC''') is an annual conference on [[virtual reality]] organized by the [[Association for Computing Machinery]]. Papers are on a variety of topics, such as mixed reality, [[human-computer interaction]], 3D interaction evaluation, and [[image analysis]]. Its proceedings are published in the [[ACM Digital Library]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2466816&picked=prox |title=Proceedings of the Virtual Reality International Conference: Laval Virtual |publisher=[[ACM Digital Library]] |date=2013-03-20 |accessdate=2014-03-07}}</ref> It is hosted and sponsored by [[ACM SIGGRAPH]], [[Association française de réalité virtuelle]], and [[Laval Virtual]] in city of Laval, France.

